The paper discusses resource allocation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The use of stable matching, factor-graph-based message passing, and distributed auctions suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY).
